sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT student_id) AS total_students_enrolled
FROM enrollments
WHERE year = 2022 AND semester = 'Spring';

external_knowledge:
- "young saplings" refers to undergraduate students;
- "sprouted and received a mark" means students who have enrolled and received a grade;
- "latest season of the academic garden" refers to the most recent year in the enrollments data.

- "Nurturing the most vibrant courses" refers to departments with a higher number of courses and a higher average capacity;
- "Latest blossoms to have been pruned" refers to the most recently updated courses in the database;
- "Pruned" refers to the last update time of the courses.
